ampionship]]: [[2004 UEFA European Football Championship|2004]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.aggelosbasinas.gr/ |title=Official Website |access-date=5 June 2007 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070605230744/http://www.aggelosbasinas.gr/ |archive-date=5 June 2007 |url-status=dead }}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-sports}}\n{{succession box|title=[[Greece national football team|Greece]] [[Captain (association football)|captain]]|before=[[Theodoros Zagorakis]]|after=[[Giorgos Karagounis]]|years=2006\u20132009}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title=Greece squads\n|bg=#0000cd\n|fg=#FFFFFF\n|list1=\n{{Greece Squad 2004 European Championship}}\n{{Greece Squad 2005 Confederations Cup}}\n{{Greece Squad 2008 Euro Cup}} }}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2011}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Basinas, Angelos}}\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Greek footballers]]\n[[Category:Greek expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:La Liga players]]\n[[Category:AEK Athens F.C. players]]\n[[Category:RCD Mallorca players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n[[Category:Panathinaikos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Portsmouth F.C. players]]\n[[Category:AC Arles-Avignon players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2004 players]]\n[[Category:2005 FIFA Confederations Cup players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2008 players]]\n[[Category:UEFA European Championship-winning players]]\n[[Category:Greece international footballers]]\n[[Category:Greece under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Super League Greece players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 1 players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in France]]\n[[Category:FIFA Century Club]]\n[[Category:People from Chalcis]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Angelos Basinas\n| image = Basinas 2008.jpg\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1976|1|3}}\n| birth_place = [[Chalkida]], Greece\n| height = 1.80 m\n| position = [[Defensive midfielder]]\n| currentclub =  \n| clubnumber =\n| years1 = 1995\u20132005 |clubs1 = [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] |caps1 = 199 |goals1 = 27\n| years2 = 2005\u20132008 |clubs2 = [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]] |caps2 = 75 |goals2 = 1\n| years3 = 2008\u20132009 |clubs3 = [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]] |caps3 = 14 |goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2009\u20132010 |clubs4 = [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]] |caps4 = 15 |goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2010\u20132011 |clubs5 = [[AC Arles-Avignon|Arles-Avignon]] |caps5 = 4 |goals5 = 0\n| totalcaps  = 307 |totalgoals = 28\n| nationalyears1 = 1999\u20132009 |nationalteam1 = [[Greece national football team|Greece]] |nationalcaps1 = 100 |nationalgoals1 = 7\n| pcupdate = {{date|2010-05-17}}\n| ntupdate = {{date|2009-04-01}}\n| medaltemplates = {{Medal|Sport|Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{fb|GRE}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[UEFA European Championship]]}}\n{{medal|W|[[UEFA Euro 2004|2004 Portugal]]|}}\n}}\n\n'''Angelos Basinas''' ({{lang-el|\u0386\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2 \u039c\u03c0\u03b1\u03c3\u03b9\u03bd\u03ac\u03c2}} {{IPA-el|\u02c8a\u0272\u025felos basi\u02c8nas|pron}}, born on 3 January 1976 in [[Chalkida]], Greece) is a retired [[Greeks|Greek]] international [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[defensive midfielder]]. He can also operate as a [[central midfielder]] and a [[centre back]]. He is best remembered for his key role in the [[Greece national football team|Greek national team]] that won the [[UEFA Euro 2004|2004 European Championship]]. He provided the header through which Angelos Charisteas scored the winning goal in the Euro 2004 Final against Portugal.\n\n==Club career==\n===Panathinaikos===\nBasinas started his career with Greek side [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]], during his time at Panathinaikos he won both the [[Superleague Greece|league]] and the [[Greek Cup]] in 2004.\nAfter a row broke out between Basinas, the manager and the Panathinaikos board over wages, Basinas was released on 21 September 2005, which brought an end to a career at the club which lasted over 10 years, during this time he made over 150 appearances for the club scoring many crucial goals both domestically and in European competitions.<ref>[http://www.uefa.com/competitions/ucl/news/kind=1/newsid=343211.html Basinas quits PAO]</ref> ( He played 153 games (26 goals, 5 assists) with the club in all competitions).\n\n===Mallorca===\nAlthough rumored to go to [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]], [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]] and [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] during the 2006 Winter transfer window, Basinas signed a contract with [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]] preferring to leave Greece and join the Spanish [[La Liga|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]].\nIn the second half of the 05/06 season, Basinas completed a successful first period at Mallorca, helping to save the team from relegation proving a key part of the struggling teams survival.\nIn his second year at the club he helped the team to finish in 7th position, one point from European  qualification.\nHe was released by Mallorca on 1 July 2008 after his 2\u00bd years' contract came to an end. He played 81 games (1 goals, 1 assists) with the club in all competitions.\n\n===AEK Athens===\nOn 31 July 2008 he signed a 3-year contract of \u20ac1.4 million per annum with [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]],<ref>[http://www.aekfc.gr/index.asp?a_id=74&n_id=4307 AEK FC sign Basinas] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080805100604/http://www.aekfc.gr/index.asp?a_id=74&n_id=4307 |date=5 August 2008 }}</ref> choosing the number 14. Despite the pre-season odds, AEK underachieved during the first half of the season and lost the title race too early, making Basinas favourable towards a new move during the winter transfer period.\n\n===Portsmouth===\nOn 2 February 2009, [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]] confirmed the signing of Basinas on an eighteen-month contract.<ref>[http://www.portsmouthfc.co.uk/index.php?cms_ref=news&qs_article_id=2129 Basinas joins Blues] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090206044940/http://www.portsmouthfc.co.uk/index.php?cms_ref=news&qs_article_id=2129 |date=6 February 2009 }}</ref> He made his debut for Portsmouth on 7 February 2009 against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]. Just a few hours after his debut, manager [[Tony Adams (footballer)|Tony Adams]], who brought Basinas in, was sacked by the club and replaced by [[Paul Hart]]. Under the new manager, Basinas hardly played and was benched for the rest of the season after only making 3 appearances for Portsmouth. Despite little playing time in his first season at Portsmouth, Basinas stated that he wanted to stay at the club.<ref>[http://www.portsmouth.co.uk/frattonlatest/Basinas-I39ll-show-you-I39m.5458562.jp Basinas staying at Portsmouth]</ref> When [[Avram Grant]] became the manager of the club, Basinas had continued to impress for Portsmouth when called upon and a poll among Portsmouth fans on 23 January 2010, showed that he's appreciated by the fans. 77% of fans believe that \"Basinas has the creative touch and must play\", while only 2% believed he should leave the club.<ref>[http://www.portsmouth.vitalfootball.co.uk/sitepage.asp?a=185578 \"NO Basinas in Pompey's FA Cup plans?\" Vitalfootball.co.uk] 23 January 2010. Accessed 23 January 2010.</ref> With Portsmouth Angelos Basinas reached the [[2010 FA Cup Final]] against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] of [[Carlo Ancelotti]].\n\n===AC Arles-Avignon===\nIn the summer 2010, Angelos Basinas moved to [[AC Arles-Avignon|Arles]], with his teammate [[Angelos Charisteas]], in the [[Ligue 1]]. He made his debut on 21 August 2010 in a 1\u20132 away defeat against [[Toulouse F.C.|Toulouse]]. Basinas made a total of five appearances in League 1 and [[Coupe de France|French Cup]]. The contract was broken two months later.\n\n==International career==\nBasinas won his first cap in a 3\u20131 win over El Salvador on 18 August 1999 and scored his first goal in just his second match, also against El Salvador just two days later. He has remained a part of the national team setup since his debut and has been a regular since [[Otto Rehhagel]] took over in 2001.\n\nHe was a key player in Greece's upset [[UEFA Euro 2004|European Championship]] victory, scoring a [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty]] in his country's 2\u20131 upset win over host team [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] in the tournament's opening game. Basinas was a vital player in the hard working midfield of the Greek team throughout the tournament. In the final, [[Charisteas]] scored the winning goal for Greece against Portugal off a corner kick by Basinas, which saw Greece win the trophy.\n\nAfter [[Theodoros Zagorakis]] retired, Basinas was selected to take the captains arm band. Basinas earned his 100th cap for Greece 1 April 2009 in a [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification|FIFA World Cup 2010 qualifier]] against [[Israel national football team|Israel]]. At the time, he was only the second Greek player to achieve [[List of Greece international footballers|100 national team appearances]] alongside Theodoros Zagorakis.\n\n==Career statistics==\n<ref>{{NFT player|id=2654|accessdate=}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Club performance\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | Cup\n! colspan=2 | League Cup\n! colspan=2 | Continental\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n! Season\n! Club\n! League\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n|-\n! colspan=3 |Greece\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | [[Greek Football Cup|Greek Cup]]\n! colspan=2 | League Cup\n! colspan=2 | [[UEFA|Europe]]\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n|[[1995\u201396 Alpha Ethniki|1995\u201396]]||rowspan=\"11\"|[[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]||rowspan=\"11\"|[[Superleague Greece|Alpha Ethniki]]||1||0||1||0||-||