h 'Asian Film Festival' \n|<ref>{{cite news |script-title=bn:\u09ae\u09c1\u09ae\u09cd\u09ac\u09be\u0987\u09af\u09bc\u09c7 \u09aa\u09c1\u09b0\u09b8\u09cd\u0995\u09be\u09b0 \u09aa\u09c7\u09b2 \u099c\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u0995\u09bf\u09b0 \u0986\u09b2\u09cb |trans-title=Mumbai Awarded Jonakir Alo |url=http://www.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/article/126880/%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%87%E0%A7%9F%E0%A7%87_%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0_%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B2_%E0%A6%9C%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%B0_%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%B2%E0%A7%8B |language=bn |newspaper=Prothom Alo |date=20 January 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Maa er Momota'' || || [[Nipun Akter]]\n|| Mostafizur Rahman Babu  \n|| Released on 25 April 2014 \n|<ref>{{cite news |script-title=bn:\u0986\u0997\u09be\u09ae\u09c0\u0995\u09be\u09b2 \u09ae\u09c1\u0995\u09cd\u09a4\u09bf \u09aa\u09be\u099a\u09cd\u099b\u09c7 \\'\u09ae\u09be\u09af\u09bc\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ae\u09ae\u09a4\u09be\\' |trans-title=Release tomorrow 'Maa er Momota' |url=http://www.kalerkantho.com/online/entertainment/2014/04/24/76521/print |language=bn |newspaper=Kaler Kantho |date=24 April 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Jaan'' || || Bindia || G Sarker || Released on 2 May 2014\n|\n|-\n| ''Kokhono Bhule Jeo Na'' || || Tani, Pushpita || Mostafizur Rahman Babu || Released on 22 August 2014 \n|\n|-\n| ''Jane Na E Mon''   \n|| || Jaanvi   \n|| M A Rahim   \n|| Released on 31 October 2014\n|\n|-\n| ''Shopno Je Tui'' || Tom\n|| [[Achol]] || Monirul Islam Shohel || Released on 7 November 2014\n|\n|-\n| ''Hridoye 71'' || || Romana || Sadeq Siddiqui || Released on 13 December 2014 \n|<ref>{{cite news |script-title=bn:\u0986\u099c \u09ae\u09c1\u0995\u09cd\u09a4\u09bf \u09aa\u09be\u099a\u09cd\u099b\u09c7 '\u09b9\u09c3\u09a6\u09af\u09bc\u09c7 \u09ed\u09e7' |trans-title='Hridoye 71' Released Today |url=http://www.bd-pratidin.com/entertainment/2014/12/12/49470 |language=bn |newspaper=Bangladesh Pratidin |date=12 December 2014 |access-date=5 January 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" | 2015 || ''Putro Ekhon Poishawala'' ||  || Shaina Amin || Nargis Akter ||\n|\n|-\n| ''Bhul Jodi Hoy''bang\n|\n| [[Alisha Pradhan]]\n| [[Chashi Nazrul Islam]]\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''Ontorongo''\n|\n| [[Alisha Pradhan]]\n| [[Chashi Nazrul Islam]]\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''Porobashinee''\n|\n| [[Mehazabien]]\n| Swapan Ahmed\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''Podmo Patar Jol''\n| Kobi\n| [[Bidya Sinha Mim]]\n| Tonmoy Tansen\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''Achena Hridoy''\n|\n|\n| Shafiqul Islam Mithu\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''Purno Doirgho Prem Kahini 2 ''\n|\n| Shakib Khan, Joya Ahsan\n| Shafi Uddin Shafi\n|\n|<ref>{{cite news |script-title=bn:\u098f\u0987 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u09b6\u09be\u0995\u09bf\u09ac-\u0987\u09ae\u09a8 |trans-title=This is the first Shakib-Emon |url=http://www.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/article/295870/%E0%A6%8F%E0%A6%87-%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%A5%E0%A6%AE-%E0%A6%B6%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AC-%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%A8 |language=bn |work=[[Prothom Alo]] |date=20 August 2014 |access-date=10 January 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"9\"|2019 || ''[[Password (2019 Bangladeshi film)|Password]]'' || Rusho || [[Shakib Khan]], [[Shabnom Bubly]] || [[Malek Afsari]] || || \n<ref>{{cite web |title= \u0987\u09ae\u09a8\u09c7\u09b0 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09b6\u0982\u09b8\u09be\u09af\u09bc \u09aa\u099e\u09cd\u099a\u09ae\u09c1\u0996 \u09b6\u09be\u0995\u09bf\u09ac \u0996\u09be\u09a8 |url= https://www.jagonews24.com/entertainment/news/499609 |website= jagonews24.com |accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"|Year\n! scope=\"col\"|Award\n! scope=\"col\"|Category\n! scope=\"col\"|Film\n! scope=\"col\"|Result\n|-\n| 2008 || [[Meril Prothom Alo Awards]] || Best Film Actor || ''Ek Buk BHalobasha'' || {{nom}}\n|- \n| 2009 || [[Meril Prothom Alo Awards]] || Best Film Actor ||  || {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2010 || [[Meril Prothom Alo Awards]] || Best Film Actor || [[Gohine Shobdo]] || {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2011 || Diamond World Channel I Best Award || Best Film Actor || ''Garments Konna'' || {{won}}\n|-\n| 2012 || [[Meril Prothom Alo Awards]] || Best Film Actor || ''[[Lal Tip]]'' || {{nom}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Cinema of Bangladesh]]\n* [[Dhallywood]]\n* [[Arifin Shuvoo]]\n* [[Ananta Jalil]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=nm4087109}}\n* [https://www.facebook.com/OfficialMamnun Mamnun Hasan Emon] on [[Facebook]]\n{{Portal bar|Biography||Bangladesh|Film}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Emon, Mamnun}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi male film actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Dhaka]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi male television actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = Mamnun Hasan Emon\n| image       = Mamnun Hasan Emon (Cropped).jpg\n| caption     = Emon in 2018\n| years_active = 2006\u2013present\n| occupation   = Actor\n| nationality  = Bangladeshi\n}}\n\n'''Mamnun Hasan Emon'''  is a Bangladeshi film actor and model.\n\n==Career==\nEmon began his career in [[Tauquir Ahmed]]'s 2007 film ''[[Daruchini Dip]]''. He earned widespread recognition in 2010 for his performance in the film ''[[Gohine Shobdo|Gohine Shobdo: Dark Renosance]]'';<ref name=\"Gohine Shobdo\">{{cite news|title=Gohine Shobdo selected in Silent River Film Fest |url=http://news.priyo.com/entertainment/2011/08/09/gohine-shobdo-selected-silent-34123.html |newspaper=Priyo |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150216220539/http://news.priyo.com/entertainment/2011/08/09/gohine-shobdo-selected-silent-34123.html |archive-date=16 February 2015 |accessdate=16 July 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref>  This performance won him several awards at the [[International Film Festival]],{{Citation needed|date=July 2013}} South Asian Film Festival,{{Citation needed|date=July 2013}} and [[Silent River Film Festival]].{{Citation needed|date=July 2013}} He achieved further success with his film ''[[Lal Tip|Lal Tip: The Red Point]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title=EMON @ DS CAFE |url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/newDesign/news-details.php?nid=226409 |newspaper=The Daily Star |date=16 March 2012 |accessdate=16 July 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, with Bangla Vision, he performed in a dramatic [[Thriller (genre)|thriller]] in Qatar titled ''Valentine'', appearing alongside Sarika and Shahnur. It was directed by M-SIB. M-SIB showed the pair of Emon and Sarika together for the first time on TV screens.<ref name=ProthomAlo>{{cite news |script-title=bn:\u098f\u0987 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u099c\u09c1\u099f\u09bf \u09b9\u09b2\u09c7\u09a8 \u0987\u09ae\u09a8-\u09b8\u09be\u09b0\u09bf\u0995\u09be |trans-title=This is the first time the pair Emon-Sarika |url=http://www.prothom-alo.com/detail/date/2012-11-04/news/302668 |language=bn |newspaper=Prothom Alo |date=11 April 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106233243/http://www.prothom-alo.com/detail/date/2012-11-04/news/302668 |archivedate=6 November 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nEmon is married to Aysha Islam since 15 February 2009. The couple have two sons, Samin and Shayan.<ref>{{cite news |script-title=bn:\u09ac\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ac\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u09b7\u09bf\u0995\u09c0\u09a4\u09c7\u0987 \u09ac\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09c7\u09b0 \u0996\u09ac\u09b0! |url=http://www.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/article/452725/%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BC%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B7%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%87-%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BC%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%96%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%B0 |language=bn |work=Prothom Alo |date=16 February 2015 |access-date=16 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"|Year\n! scope=\"col\"|Film\n! scope=\"col\"|Role\n! scope=\"col\"|Co-artist\n! scope=\"col\"|Director\n! scope=\"col\"|Notes\n!Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2007 || ''[[Daruchini Dip]]'' || Shonju || [[Riaz (actor)|Riaz]], Momo, Bindu || [[Tauquir Ahmed]] ||\n|\n|-\n| ''Ek Buk Bhalobasa'' || Emon || [[Apu Biswas]]\n|| Ispahani Arif Zaman ||\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|2009\n| ''Rastar Chele''\n|\n| Sahara\n| Shahin Sumon\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''Sobai To Bhalobasha Chay''\n|\n| [[Purnima]]\n| Delowar Jahan Jhantu\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''Piritir Agun Jole Digun''\n|\n| Shabnur, Afsana Ara Bindu\n| P A Kajol\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2010 || ''Panch Takar Prem'' || || Resi || ||\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Gohine Shobdo]]'' || Niloy || Kusum Shikder || Khalid Mahmud Mithu || \n|\n|-\n| ''Mayer Jonno Morte Pari'' || || Resi || Ahmed Nasir || \n|\n|-\n| ''Jemon Jamai Temon Bou''\n|\n| Chandni\n| Uttam Akash\n| Released on 17 December 2010 \n|<ref>{{cite news|title=Jemon Jamai Temon Bou |script-title=bn:\u09af\u09c7\u09ae\u09a8 \u099c\u09be\u09ae\u09be\u0987 \u09a4\u09c7\u09ae\u09a8 \u09ac\u0989 |url=http://www.banglanews24.com/LifeStyle/detailsnews.php?nssl=543 |language=bn |work=banglanews24.com |date=29 October 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103072510/http://www.banglanews24.com/LifeStyle/detailsnews.php?nssl=543 |archive-date=3 January 2015 |access-date=3 January 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |2011\n| ''Ma er Jonno Pagol''\n|\n| Nodi\n| Ahmed Nasir\n|\n|\n|-\n|''Gariber Bhai''\n|\n| Romana\n| P A Kajol\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''Amar Prithibi Tumi''\n|\n| Sahara\n| Gazi Mahbub\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''Angko''\n|\n| Ratna\n| Shahin Sumon\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''Garments Konna''\n|\n| Popy\n| G Sarker\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2012 || ''[[Lal Tip]]'' || Arnab || Kusum Shikder || Swapan Ahmed || ||\n|-\n| ''Maruf er Challenge''\n|\n| Nipun Akter\n| Shahadat Hossain Liton\n|\n| \n|-\n| ''Tumi Sondharo Meghmala''\n|\n| Bidya Sinha Mim\n| Ripon Miah\n| Unreleased\n| \n|-\n| ''Shiulimoni''\n|\n| Nipun Akter\n| Sadeq Siddqui\n| \n| \n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 2013 || ''Eito Bhalobasha'' ||  || [[Nipun Akter]], Nirab Hossain [[Alisha Pradhan]] as guest appearance || Shaheen Kabir Tutul || <ref>{{cite web |url=http://sharemarket24.com/bangla/2013/05/10/4506/ |script-title=bn:\u098f\u0987 \u09a4\u09cb \u09ad\u09be\u09b2\u09cb\u09ac\u09be\u09b8\u09be' \u0986\u09b8\u099b\u09c7 \u09e8\u09ea \u09ae\u09c7 \u0985\u09a4\u09bf\u09a5\u09bf \u099a\u09b0\u09bf\u09a4\u09cd\u09b0\u09c7 \u0986\u09b2\u09bf\u09b6\u09be \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a7\u09be\u09a8 |trans-title=Ei to Bhalobasha releases on 24th may, Alisha Pradhan's guest appearance |website=sharemarket24.com |language=bn}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" | 2014 || ''[[Jonakir Alo]]'' || || [[Bidya Sinha Mim]] || Khalid Mahmud Mithu\n|| The film got 'Audience Choice Award' <br />in 12th 'Asian Film Festival' \n|<ref>{{cite news |script-title=bn:\u09ae\u09c1\u09ae\u09cd\u09ac\u09be\u0987\u09af\u09bc\u09c7 \u09aa\u09c1\u09b0\u09b8\u09cd\u0995\u09be\u09b0 \u09aa\u09c7\u09b2 \u099c\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u0995\u09bf\u09b0 \u0986\u09b2\u09cb |trans-title=Mumbai Awarded Jonakir Alo |url=http://www.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/article/126880/%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%87%E0%A7%9F%E0%A7%87_%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0_%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B2_%E0%A6%9C%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%B0_%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%B2%E0%A7%8B |language=bn |newspaper=Prothom Alo |date=20 January 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Maa er Momota'' || || [[Nipun Akter]]\n|| Mostafizur Rahman Babu  \n|| Released on 25 April 2014 \n|<ref>{{cite news |script-title=bn:\u0986\u0997\u09be\u09ae\u09c0\u0995\u09be\u09b2 \u09ae\u09c1\u0995\u09cd\u09a4\u09bf \u09aa\u09be\u099a\u09cd\u099b\u09c7 \\'\u09ae\u09be\u09af\u09bc\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ae\u09ae\u09a4\u09be\\' |trans-title=Release tomorrow 'Maa er Momota' |url=http://www.kalerkantho.com/online/entertainment/2014/04/24/76521/print |language=bn |newspaper=Kaler Kantho |da