{"title_page": "Trevor Long (actor)", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Trevor Long\n| image         = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date    = \n| birth_place   = \n| nationality   = [[United States|American]]\n| alma_mater    = \n| occupation    = [[Actor]]\n| years_active  = 1994&ndash;present\n| website       = \n}}\n'''Trevor Long''' is an American film, television and stage actor, best known for his recurring role as Cade Langmore on the [[Netflix]] TV series ''[[Ozark (TV series)|Ozark]]'', as well as his role as former detective Sean Foster on the television series ''[[Low Winter Sun]]''. \n\n== Early Life ==\n\nLong was born in [[Poughkeepsie, New York|Poughkeepsie]], [[New York  (state)|New York]] and moved to [[Pittsburgh]], [[Pennsylvania]] in second grade, graduating from [[Sewickley Academy]] in 1988.<ref name=\"sewickley\">{{cite web|url=https://issuu.com/sewickley_academy/docs/77247_print_mang_sewickley_web/68|title=Trevor Long '88 Resident Bad Boy|accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref>Long completed his Bachelor of Arts in acting at [[Brown University]] and his Masters of Fine Arts in [[Meisner technique| Meisner acting]] at [[Rutgers University]].<ref name=\"backstage\">{{cite web|url=https://www.backstage.com/u/TrevorLong/|title=Trevor Long|accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref name=\"huntington\">{{cite web|url=https://www.huntingtontheatre.org/artists/trevor-long/|title=Trevor Long|accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref> He also trained with [[Harold Guskin]].<ref name=\"huntington\" />\n\n== Career==\n\n=== Film ===\n\nLong's notable film credits include ''[[Killing Them Softly]]'', ''[[Don Juan DeMarco]]'', and ''[[Jack Goes Boating (film)|Jack Goes Boating]]''. in 2018, he starred in ''Seeds'', a horror film directed by his brother, Owen.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehollywoodnews.com/2018/09/04/exclusive-interviews-seeds-director-owen-long-stars-trevor-long-andrea-chen/2/|title=Exclusive Interviews: \u2018Seeds\u2019 Director Owen Long & Stars Trevor Long & Andrea Chen|date=2018-09-04|accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref> <ref name=\"aesthetic\">{{cite web|url=https://aestheticmagazinetoronto.com/2018/10/12/interview-trevor-long-ozark-netflix/|title=Interview: Trevor Long Talks \u201cOzark\u201d Season Two, and What He\u2019s Binge Watching on Netflix|date=2018-10-12|accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n=== Stage ===\n\nLong has also been involved in numerous off-Broadway and other theater performances with the [[Huntington Theatre Company]] in [[Boston]], the [[Manhattan Theatre Club]], and the the [[LAByrinth Theater Company]] in [[New York City]], where he starred in a production of [[In Arabia We'd All Be Kings]] directed by [[Philip Seymour Hoffman]].<ref name=\"amc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amc.com/shows/low-winter-sun/talk/2013/09/qa-trevor-long-sean-foster|title=Q&A \u2013 Trevor Long (Sean Foster)|accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref> \n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[Don Juan DeMarco]]''\n| Waiter\n|\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''Pit''\n| Dale\n| Short\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''Fat Cats''\n| Prison inmate\n| \n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[The Karaoke King]]''\n| Tommy\n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Brutal Massacre|Brutal Massacre: A Comedy]]''\n| Ronaldo\n|\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''Concerto''\n| Phillip\n| Short\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''The Roofer''\n| Miles\n| Short\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Jack Goes Boating (film)|Jack Goes Boating]]''\n| Waldorf Doorman\n| \n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Tymbals''\n| ROLE\n| \n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Killing Them Softly]]''\n| Steve Caprio\n| \n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[What Maisie Knew (film)|What Maisie Knew]]''\n| Musician #1\n| \n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Armed Defense''\n| Man\n| Short\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Low Winter Sun]]''\n| Sean Foster\n| 7 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[The Blacklist (TV series)|The Blacklist]]''\n| Alan Ray Rifkin\n| Episode: \"[[The Judge (The Blacklist)|The Judge]]\"\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Blindspot (TV series)|Blindspot]]''\n| Boyce\n| Episode: \"Pilot\"\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Unforgettable (U.S. TV series)|Unforgettable]]''\n| Foster Lee Nolan\n| Episode: \"Game On\"\n|-\n| 2017\u20132018\n| ''[[Ozark (TV series)|Ozark]]''                  \n| Cade Langmore\n| 13 episodes\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''Seeds''\n| Marcus\n| \n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Magnum P.I. (2018 TV series)|Magnum P.I.]]''\n| Manny\n| Episode: \"Die He Said\"\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Chicago P.D. (TV series)|Chicago P.D.]]''\n| Logan Gaines\n| Episode: \"Ties That Bind\"\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Bull (2016 TV series)|Bull]]''\n| Norman Schweiger\n| Episode: \"Parental Guidance\"\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[The Resident (TV series)|The Resident]]''\n| Rob Spiro\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[FBI: Most Wanted]]''\n| Gil Rickman\n| Episode: \"Dopesick\"\n|}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|0519217}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Long, Trevor}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n\n\n{{US-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{No footnotes|BLP=yes|date=January 2014}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Trevor Long\n| image         = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date    = \n| birth_place   = \n| nationality   = [[United States|American]]\n| alma_mater    = \n| occupation    = [[Actor]]\n| years_active  = 1994&ndash;present\n| website       = \n}}\n'''Trevor Long''' is an American film, television and stage actor, best known for his recurring role as Cade Langmore on the [[Netflix]] TV series ''[[Ozark (TV series)|Ozark]]'', as well as his role as former detective Sean Foster on the television series ''[[Low Winter Sun]]''. \n\n== Early Life ==\n\nLong was born in [[Poughkeepsie, New York|Poughkeepsie]], [[New York  (state)|New York]] and moved to [[Pittsburgh]], [[Pennsylvania]] in second grade, graduating from [[Sewickley Academy]] in 1988.<ref name=\"sewickley\">{{cite web|url=https://issuu.com/sewickley_academy/docs/77247_print_mang_sewickley_web/68|title=Trevor Long '88 Resident Bad Boy|accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref>Long completed his Bachelor of Arts in acting at [[Brown University]] and his Masters of Fine Arts in [[Meisner technique| Meisner acting]] at [[Rutgers University]].<ref name=\"backstage\">{{cite web|url=https://www.backstage.com/u/TrevorLong/|title=Trevor Long|accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref name=\"huntington\">{{cite web|url=https://www.huntingtontheatre.org/artists/trevor-long/|title=Trevor Long|accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref> He also trained with [[Harold Guskin]].<ref name=\"huntington\" />\n\n== Career==\n\n=== Film ===\n\nLong's notable film credits include ''[[Killing Them Softly]]'', ''[[Don Juan DeMarco]]'', and ''[[Jack Goes Boating (film)|Jack Goes Boating]]''. in 2018, he starred in ''Seeds'', a horror film directed by his brother, Owen.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehollywoodnews.com/2018/09/04/exclusive-interviews-seeds-director-owen-long-stars-trevor-long-andrea-chen/2/|title=Exclusive Interviews: \u2018Seeds\u2019 Director Owen Long & Stars Trevor Long & Andrea Chen|date=2018-09-04|accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref> <ref name=\"aesthetic\">{{cite web|url=https://aestheticmagazinetoronto.com/2018/10/12/interview-trevor-long-ozark-netflix/|title=Interview: Trevor Long Talks \u201cOzark\u201d Season Two, and What He\u2019s Binge Watching on Netflix|date=2018-10-12|accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n=== Stage ===\n\nLong has also been involved in numerous off-Broadway and other theater performances with the [[Huntington Theatre Company]] in [[Boston]], the [[Manhattan Theatre Club]], and the the [[LAByrinth Theater Company]] in [[New York City]], where he starred in a production of [[In Arabia We'd All Be Kings]] directed by [[Philip Seymour Hoffman]].<ref name=\"amc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amc.com/shows/low-winter-sun/talk/2013/09/qa-trevor-long-sean-foster|title=Q&A \u2013 Trevor Long (Sean Foster)|accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref> \n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n!