{"title_page": "List of Indonesian provinces by GRP per capita", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis article presents a '''list of [[provinces of Indonesia|Indonesian provinces]]''' sorted by their '''gross regional product nominal''' (GRP Nominal) per capita.\n\n== Methodology ==\nGRP Nominal is the regional or provincial counterpart of the national [[gross domestic product]], the most comprehensive measure of national economic activity. The [[Statistics Indonesia]] (''Badan Pusat Statistik'') derives GRP for a province as the sum of the GRP Nominal originating in all the industries in the province at current prices market.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bps.go.id/index.php/publikasi/4238|title=Statistik Indonesia 2016|last=|first=|date=2016|website=|publisher=Badan Pusat Statistik|location=Jakarta|language=Indonesian|format=PDF|access-date=|archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20161113201922/http://www.bps.go.id/index.php/publikasi/4238|archive-date=2016-11-13|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nList of Indonesian administrative divisions by GRP Nominal, with 14,140 IDR = US$1 term of Nominal while 4,325.87 IDR = US$1 term of PPP .<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bps.go.id/index.php/publikasi/4238 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-11-14 |archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20161113201922/http://www.bps.go.id/index.php/publikasi/4238 |archive-date=2016-11-13 |url-status=dead }}</ref>. Note some provinces have little population and large oil, gas, or mining revenues, and therefore GRP Nominal does not reflect consumer demand.\n\n{{center|{{Indonesia provinces labelled map|thumb=y|caption=This clickable map shows province of Indonesia as of 25 October 2012. Click on a province name to go to its main article.}}}}\n\n\n\n==2019 data==\n===GDP Data===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n!rowspan=\"2\" | Rank\n!rowspan=\"2\" | Province\n!rowspan=\"2\" | Region\n!rowspan=\"2\" | GDP<br>(in billion [[Indonesian rupiah|Rp]])\n!scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\"|GDP Nominal\n!scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\"|GDP PPP\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | <small>(in billion [[US Dollar|$]])</small>\n!Comparable country\n! scope=\"col\" | <small>(in billion [[US Dollar|$]])</small>\n!Comparable country\n|-\n|align=center| -\n|'''{{flag|Indonesia}}'''\n|'''[[South East Asia]]'''\n|align=right| 16,073,257\n|align=right| 1,136.72 \n|align=left| {{flag|Mexico}}\n|align=right| 3,715.61 \n|align=left| {{flag|Russia}}\n|-\n|align=center| -\n|''[[Java Island]]''\n|''[[Indonesia]]''\n|align=right| 8,887,231\n|align=right| 628.51 \n|align=left| {{flag|Switzerland}}\n|align=right| 2,054.43\n|align=left| {{flag|South Korea}}\n|-\n|align=center| -\n|''[[Sumatra Island]]''\n|''[[Indonesia]]''\n|align=right| 3,427,226\n|align=right| 242.38 \n|align=left| {{flag|Romania}}\n|align=right| 792.26\n|align=left| {{flag|South Africa}}\n|-\n|align=center| -\n|''[[Kalimantan]]''\n|''[[Indonesia]]''\n|align=right| 1,294,474\n|align=right| 91.55 \n|align=left| {{flag|Angola}}\n|align=right| 299.24\n|align=left| {{flag|Sri Lanka}}\n|-\n|align=center| -\n|''[[Sulawesi Island]]''\n|''[[Indonesia]]''\n|align=right| 1,018,122\n|align=right| 72.00 \n|align=left| {{flag|Oman}}\n|align=right| 235.36\n|align=left| {{flag|Ethiopia}}\n|-\n|align=center| -\n|''[[Lesser Sunda Islands]]''\n|''[[Indonesia]]''\n|align=right| 492,165\n|align=right| 34.81 \n|align=left| {{flag|Latvia}}\n|align=right| 113.77\n|align=left| {{flag|Panama}}\n|-\n|align=center| -\n|''[[Western New Guinea]]''\n|''[[Indonesia]]''\n|align=right| 274,064\n|align=right| 19.38\n|align=left| {{flag|Laos}}\n|align=right| 63.36\n|align=left| {{flag|Senegal}}\n|-\n|align=center| -\n|''[[Maluku Islands]]''\n|''[[Indonesia]]''\n|align=right| 85,973\n|align=right| 6.08\n|align=left| {{flag|Maldives}}\n|align=right| 19.87\n|align=left| {{flag|Iceland}}\n|-\n|align=center| 1\n|{{flag|Jakarta}}\n|[[Java]]\n|align=right| 2,840,828\n|align=right| 200.91 \n|align=left| {{flag|New Zealand}}\